{
  "texts": [
    "In what follows, we focus on the GWB generated by decaying (M)HD turbulence.",
    "The presence of bulk velocity and magnetic fields produce anisotropic stresses, which in turn act as a source of GWs (Kamionkowski et al. 1994; Kosowsky et al. 2002; Dolgov et al. 2002; Caprini & Durrer 2006; Gogoberidze et al. 2007; Caprini et al. 2009).",
    "This has been recently studied via numerical simulations in Roper Pol et al. (2020a Pol et al. (,b, 2022a)), Brandenburg et al. (2021).",
    "In particular, Roper Pol et al. (2022a) show that the envelope of the GWB produced by decaying MHD turbulence can be estimated analytically, assuming that the anisotropic stresses from the velocity and magnetic fields vary more slowly than the dynamical production of GWs.",
    "This was also validated by numerical simulations of purely kinetic turbulence in Auclair et al. (2022)."
  ]
}